                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="13712544" author="alex.franchuk" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2013 18:41:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to fix the problem, using the CSVUtils class from solr-commons-csv.jar&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13713367" author="tdunning" created="Fri, 19 Jul 2013 07:12:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Is that a new dependency?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13713667" author="alex.franchuk" created="Fri, 19 Jul 2013 14:49:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I saw that this library was in the mahout distribution&apos;s lib folder, so its not a new dependency for mahout. For the file in particular, yes it is.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13713787" author="tdunning" created="Fri, 19 Jul 2013 16:59:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Excellent news.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As soon as the 0.8 release finishes we can commit this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for cleaning up the overly simple implementation that I put down in the first place.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13714057" author="alex.franchuk" created="Fri, 19 Jul 2013 21:51:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;No problem. I&apos;m just glad it&apos;s getting out there so others can have an easier time with it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, the same solution can be used to standardize the csv parsing of the classifier.df.DataLoader and classifier.df.DataConverter classes, which actually split up fields based on commas or spaces... although I&apos;m not sure how maintained those classes are at the moment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13721528" author="smarthi" created="Sat, 27 Jul 2013 06:11:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=alex.franchuk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;alex.franchuk&quot;&gt;Alex Franchuk&lt;/a&gt; I committed this patch to trunk, I had to add Solr 4.3 solr-common-csv.jar to core/pom.xml. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
